    <methods>
      <methodStep>
        <description>
          <para>
  At each quadrat location, 4 cores were collected at bare
  (non-vegetated) areas at 2 depths: 0-5cm and 5-20cm, stacked on top of
  each other. The 0-5cm deep core had a diameter of 6.1cm and the 5-20cm
  core had a diameter of 4.6cm. Samples were air dried at room
  temperature, then hand sieved to 2mm to remove large organic material
  and the &amp;gt;2mm fraction. Particle size analysis by the hydrometer
  method was performed on a ~60g subsample. Sand left over from the
  hydrometer analysis (&amp;gt;53µm fraction) was washed through a 53µm
  sieve, dried at 105C for 24h to remove moisture, then separated into 5
  sand size classes (53-106 micrometers, 106-250 micrometers, 250-500
  micrometers, 500-1000 micrometers, 1000-2000 micrometers) in an
  ultrasonic sifter for 5 minutes and weighed.
</para>
          <para>
  Most soil samples were collected at various times throughout 2000.
  Those collected in 2020 were all collected on February 7, 2020.
</para>
        </description>
      </methodStep>
    </methods>
